info.guardianproject.otr.app.im.engine

Interface ContactListListener


  • public interface ContactListListener
    Interfaces that allows the implementing classes to listen to contact list relative events. Listeners are registered with ContactListManager.

    • Method Detail

      • onContactChange

        void onContactChange(int type,
                     ContactList list,
                     Contact contact)
        Called when:
        • a contact list has been created, deleted, renamed or loaded, or
        • a contact has been added to or removed from a list, or
        • a contact has been blocked or unblocked
        Parameters:
        type - one of the following values:
        • LIST_CREATED list: the newly created list; contact: null
        • LIST_DELETED list: the delete list; contact: null
        • LIST_LOADED list: the newly loaded list; contact: null
        • LIST_RENAMED list: the list renamed; contact: null
        • LIST_CONTACT_ADDED list: the list to which the contact is added, contact: the added contact
        • LIST_CONTACT_REMOVED list: the list from which the contact is removed, contact: the removed contact
        • CONTACT_BLOCKED list: null, contact: the blocked contact
        • CONTACT_UNBLOCKED list: null, contact: the unblocked contact
        list -
        contact -

      • onAllContactListsLoaded

        void onAllContactListsLoaded()
        Called when all the contact lists (including the block list) and contacts have been loaded from the server.

      • onContactsPresenceUpdate

        void onContactsPresenceUpdate(Contact[] contacts)
        Called when received one or more contacts' updated presence information from the server.
        Parameters:
        contacts - one or more contacts that have updated presence information.

      • onContactError

        void onContactError(int errorType,
                    ImErrorInfo error,
                    java.lang.String listName,
                    Contact contact)
        Parameters:
        errorType - one of the following values:
        • ERROR_CREATING_LIST listName: the name of the list to be created; contact: null
        • ERROR_DELETING_LIST listName: the name of the list to be deleted; contact: null
        • ERROR_LOADING_LIST listName: the name of the list to be loaded, or null if the error occurred while fetching the list of contact lists; contact: null
        • ERROR_RENAMING_LIST listName: the original name of the list to be renamed; contact: null
        • ERROR_LOADING_BLOCK_LIST list: null; contact: null
        • ERROR_RETRIEVING_PRESENCE
          • when retrieving presence for a list: listName: the name of the list, or null, depending on the implementation; contact: null
          • when retrieving presence for a contact: listName: the name of the list that the contact belongs to, or null, depending on the implementation; contact: the contact
        • ERROR_ADDING_CONTACT listName: the name of the list to which the contact was to be added; contact: the contact to add
        • ERROR_REMOVING_CONTACT listName: the name of the list from which the contact was to be removed; contact: the contact to remove
        • ERROR_BLOCKING_CONTACT list: null; contact: the contact to block
        • ERROR_UNBLOCKING_CONTACT list: null; contact: the contact to be unblocked
        error -
        listName -
        contact -
